Manchester City midfielder, Ilkay Gundogan, has tested positive for COVID-19, ahead of his side’s Premier League clash with Wolves on Monday night. Gundogan will now self-isolate for ten days, which will see him miss at least three games for Pep Guardiola’s side against Wolves, Bournemouth and Leicester City. Man City disclosed this in a statement via the club’s official website on Monday. “Manchester City FC can confirm that Ilkay Gundogan has tested positive for COVID-19. “Ilkay is now observing a ten-day period of self-isolation in accordance with Premier League and UK Government protocol on quarantine. “Everyone at the Club wishes Ilkay a speedy recovery.” Gundogan, 29, was a regular starter in Man City’s midfield last season as he made 49 appearances in all competitions for the Citizens.